'''Project Chubar''' was a scientific program under the command of [[Warlord/Legends|Warlord]] [[Zsinj]].

==History==
The project was originally commissioned by [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], who wanted [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]] agents with [[Human/Legends|Humanlike]] self-control. It is likely around [[5 BBY/Legends|5BBY]] when [[Zsinj]] assumed control of the project, and was as far-reaching as thousands of alien subjects by the time it was assumed by him.

Named after [[Chubar]], a character from a series of animated holoprograms for children, Project Chubar was intended to enhance the intelligence of nonhuman [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] or near-sapient beings with a variety of genetic, chemical, and behavioral techniques. These beings would then serve as agents for the organization which created them. Ironically, [[Garik Loran]], one of the new Republic operatives to later expose the project, actually voiced Chubar in his childhood.<ref name="XWSC">''[[X-Wing: Solo Command]]''</ref>

Based at the [[Binring Biomedical Product]] facility on [[Saffalore]], the project was led by Doctor [[Tuzin Gast]], who was assisted by his niece [[Edda Gast]].<ref name="XWSC" /> A facility on [[Xartun]] supplied [[Transparisteel/Legends|transparisteel]] cells for the lab.

In the case of near-sapient or less intelligent sapient lifeforms, the program increased their intellect to [[Human/Legends|Human]] standards. In the case of species that were already intelligent, the program altered the quality and specialization of intelligence characteristics to be more in line with Human brains and sometimes endowed the subject with intellect beyond that of a Human.<ref name="XWSC" />

Subjects of the program included [[Bilar]]s, [[Chadra-Fan/Legends|Chadra-Fan]], [[Ewok/Legends|Ewoks]], [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorreans]], [[Kowakian monkey-lizard/Legends|Kowakian monkey-lizards]], [[Ortolan/Legends|Ortolans]], [[Ranat/Legends|Ranats]], [[Talz/Legends|Talz]], and even [[Dianoga/Legends|Dianogas]]. Some of the subjects were [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]]. One notable success of the program was known as Subject Gamma-9104, a Gamorrean who took the name [[Voort saBinring]] when his creator allowed him to escape. Other subjects included the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Gorc]] and [[Picaroon C. Boodle|Pic]], who were further enhanced by [[Cronal|Agent Blackhole's]] [[Sith alchemy/Legends|Sith alchemy]].

The project suffered a minor setback when Tuzin Gast committed suicide by causing an explosion in the lab's Epsilon Wing, but it continued on Saffalore under Edda Gast and [[Novin Bress]].<ref name="XWSC" /> A secondary laboratory was located onboard Zsinj's flagship, [[Iron Fist (Executor-class)|''Iron Fist'']]. After Zsinj learned that [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] pilot Voort saBinring was an escapee of the program, his escape enabled by Tuzin Gast and covered up by the explosion, he had the laboratories consolidated on ''Iron Fist'' and ordered Edda Gast to turn the Saffalore facility into a trap for [[Wraith Squadron]].

A large number of subjects were released by [[Gara Petothel]], and they escaped aboard a [[Sentinel-class landing craft/Legends|''Sentinel''-class landing craft]] piloted by [[Kolot]], an Ewok subject of Project Chubar. They may have accompanied Petothel to [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]], but their fates remain unknown. Kolot at least seems to have been with Gara, since she wanted to show him to Myn Donos.

Project Chubar served as the basis for Zsinj's chemical brainwashing program, [[Project Minefield]]. The program was presumably terminated along with the rest of Zsinj's projects when ''Iron Fist'' was destroyed.

